07:38.030 --> 07:41.093
felt, which of the branches of the Army were the 
most prestigious? What was the best to be in?

07:51.032 --> 07:56.822
Well, I really don't think at A&M anybody looked at 
the best there. They looked at what people were

07:56.862 --> 08:00.990
interested in, like the cavalry. They had the 
horse-drawn cavalry then, and people that liked

08:01.030 --> 08:05.157
to ride in the cavalry or in the field artillery 
because the field artillery was horse-drawn. And

08:10.509 --> 08:27.752
that

08:10.509 --> 08:27.752
was one of the reasons I liked the field artillery 
in addition to the fact that my uncle had been, was a

08:10.509 --> 08:27.752
captain, at that time was a captain in the field 
artillery. So did you ride a good bit? Oh, yeah.

08:30.395 --> 08:31.617
