08:55.947 --> 08:57.229
on college property. It was on the other side of the 
railroad track, on the west side. But that was a lot

09:02.076 --> 09:05.340
of fun. You had asked me to think about things that 
really had prepared me in later life, and one of

09:05.801 --> 09:16.116
them was horseback riding. And this has what 
happened in 1955. I was part of a group that went to

09:24.247 --> 09:31.778
Yemen and negotiated a deal with the old king of 
Yemen. And

09:32.018 --> 09:41.111
Life magazine wrote a story about it, which I've 
told you here. But the pertinent part is that as we

09:45.678 --> 09:52.567
flew to Cairo and then to Djibouti. And the King 
sent his airplane over to Dakota or DC-3 and picked

09:53.008 --> 10:00.418
us up. And we flew into Taiz, which was his summer 
palace. And there were no hotels there at all. And

10:07.190 --> 10:09.192
we stayed at the guest house. But when we called on 
the king, I told him through the interpreter that I

10:09.212 --> 10:21.323
admired the stallions that I had seen coming up to 
Taiz. And he asked me through the interpreter, did

10:21.343 --> 10:23.945
I like to ride? And I said, yes, I did. And so the next 
morning, he sent the fieriest stallion he had down

10:26.808 --> 10:33.994
there for me to ride, a horse called Rod. 
Fortunately, the horse had a snaffle bit and a curb

10:33.974 --> 10:40.121
bit. After fighting the horse for some time, I was 
finally able to get on him and ride him off. He was up

10:51.495 --> 10:59.104
on the balcony watching, and the king sent his 
horse down every morning for me to ride. So we were

10:59.455 --> 11:01.037
there six weeks. We finally got the concession. 
And so after the concession, our interpreter

11:03.179 --> 11:10.528
said, do you know why people got this concession? I 
said, no. He said, because you could ride that

11:11.549 --> 11:13.091
horse. And he figured that if, according to the 
interpreter, that if I had not lied about being

11:14.193 --> 11:21.261
able to ride, that we possibly would observe the 
things. So here, there was this deal in Yemen. Oh,

11:35.171 --> 11:41.224
thank you, thank you,

11:35.171 --> 11:41.224
thank you.

